features: NATURAL BABY WIPES: Our aloe wipes are independently certified organic and free of harmful chemicals by Ecocert COSMOS. These hypoallergenic baby wipes are made from 100% plant based ultrathin fibers that are soft, compostable, and natural

FOR SENSITIVE SKIN: We make our baby wipes unscented and hypoallergenic to help eliminate irritants and allergens, making them the perfect newborn baby and toddler wipes. Aloe baby wipes are free of harsh or harmful chemicals, which make them healthier for babies

COMPOSTABLE AND ECO-FRIENDLY: Because of their plant-based fibers and pure water content, these eco-friendly baby wipes are certified for home compost and decompose in just 12 weeks in a standard garden composter. The packaging is made of renewable plant based materials.

CLEAN AND GREEN: Whether your baby has sensitive skin or not, using plant-based baby diaper wipes made from organic plant materials and pure water without synthetics or chemicals is simply better for their skin. Baby aloe wipes are perfect for newborns and babies.

GOOD FOR BABY, GOOD FOR NATURE: Eco by Naty was first started in Sweden nearly 27 years ago. Today, we continue with our goal to create products that are not only safe for our bodies, but that are also good for the environment. Our High-Tech Eco Products are backed by independent sustainability certifications, we offer the greenest products, all made from nature!
body.description: Give your baby’s bum the VIP treatment with our extra soft and thick wipes enriched with soothing chamomile. Naty wipes are made from natural ingredients, and are chlorine, plastic and perfume free. Our wipes have been independently certified to be 100% compostable, which means that no toxic lotions have been added that might make your tomatoes glow purple. And because they’re dermatologically tested, you can chill out about nappy rash and nasty allergic reactions too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2015
reviews.reviewText: I used these when my son was little and loved them, but then we switched to Honest all around and loved them too. We recently switched back to Naty when we canceled our Honest account, and I remembered why I loved these wipes so much. They're a lovely and very mellow little scent, smaller in size than Honest and other wipes which creates less waste, and the wetness level is neither too wet nor too dry. Additionally they are not textured like Honest and Seventh Generation, which I like.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The best! Very soft :)
reviews.reviewText: We are new parents and tried all kinds of wipes. pampers, Dove, Baby ganics from target etc and these are the best. Soft, gentle, moist and you can tell these are high-quality wipes. No allergies or rashes at all. All other brand wipes felt as if they were made out of plastic. Avoid the errors we made as new parents and get these. The best!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 26, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Thick and hard to pull apart
reviews.reviewText: As a bit of an eco warrior I wanted to love these but they’re just not as easy to use as Pampers wipes. They kind of stick together when trying to pull them out of the bag, and when you’re surrounded by poop you need that to be easy!! Also, the packs are smaller than pampers so presumably they are using more plastic packaging which kind of defeats the point? I will still be using them though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 19, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wipes that *ACTUALLY* break down
reviews.reviewText: I love these wipes, they are truly just cotton- we do cloth diapers and try to limit our waste where we can and sometimes the wipes go through the washing machine with the diapers...No other brand I’ve tried actually breaks down but these are clearly just cotton! Even Honest Co. wipes come out with little change to their shape as they went in. It’s unimaginable how many wipes are out there when they’re made from such tiny plastic threads and keep as a fabric even after going through a disinfectant wash, you could actually reuse alllllll of them it’s wild.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 10, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Not for sensitive skin, scent is awful!
reviews.reviewText: We used to use the same baby wipes 6 year ago. Now decided to use it again for our little boy. The scent is not good at all! I can’t describe it but it is not very appealing to me not even to my 6 year old. It’s soft but it stings! I used it to wipe my face and it stings not gentle at all. I stopped using it maybe just save it for messy hands. Will not use on baby bottom or face.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Part of my trifecta in caring for my little loves
reviews.reviewText: I’ve tried so many wipes and these are by far my favorite. I love that they are compostable and gentle on the skin. I don’t have to feel guilty for caring for my loves and hurting the earth now that I switched to these wipes and the DYPER nappies (diapers) which are biodegradable too! My next switch is getting away from plastic/synthetic clothes by renting to Upchoose! Just so much waste caring for children that these three companies try to combat and help the earth while caring for little ones.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2019
reviews.reviewText: Commercial-grade composting companies accept a wide variety of organic and man-made products ranging from food scraps to wax paper and paper towels. One thing they don’t accept is any kind of plastic-based material. That meant that the Huggies wipes I was so fond of for bath and baby cleanup (not diaper cleanup since that would be a biohazard and strictly verboten) had to go since they have polymer filaments woven into the cloth. The biodegradable and compostable Eco-brand wipe by Naty seemed like a good fit for my new earth-friendly lifestyle.Eco may be earth friendly, but they aren’t human friendly due to their small cloth size, a dispensing design that makes the cloths difficult to get out of the packaging one at a time, and which have only a semi-moist feel – perhaps due to the lack of quilting on the cloth. I tried and liked the Honest wipes better (see pictures comparing the packaging, design, and cloth size of both brands; Eco on left, Honest on right.)The Eco brand may work for you and your family. For my time, money, and needs it just didn’t clean up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not for sensitive skin
reviews.reviewText: I bought a case of these for my newborn because they are compostable. My baby did fine with the Huggies wipes that came from the hospital, but after we switched to these he developed horrible diaper rash. Our pediatrician recommend ointment and to stop using all wipes until it healed up. After that we started using Dyper wipes and had no problems. Ran out and went back to the Eco Naty wipes and by the end of the first day the rash started to come back. Will not be using these on my baby again. Sad that I have almost a full case left.

reviews.reviewTitle: Perfectas cuando empiezan a usar el wc
reviews.reviewText: No tienen olor fuerte, y cuando quitas el pañal y empiezan a usar el wc va perfecto porque puedes tirarlas por el wc. Llevamos usandolas 5 meses y van fenomenal, ni irritaciones ni nada.
Ich liebe diese Feuchtücher. Sie sind weich und unser Baby bekommt, anders als bei anderen Marken, keinen Ausschlag. Wir sind demnach sehr zufrieden.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on May 30, 2018
reviews.reviewText: I think the time has come one shouldn’t ignore the amount of waste we are producing on daily basis. You just have to go bio-degradable. I know it costs more than your supermarket brand, but they cost the Earth a lot more, it will cost your children more in years to come to deal with the amount of waste we have produced. Perhaps you should give up the wipes full stop, I don’t know, but definitely not the standard ones.As to product itself- it is actually not that bad- decent size pack, moist wipes, soft. The odour is not that great, but quite reasonable. I have also used them to remove makeup. Somehow I find these stinging less than some other brands. Overall I have to give it 5stars. I just hope it is not a gimmick.

These wipes are the best on the market. I have several sensitivities as do my children. These wipes are very gentle and do not contain harsh chemicals. Ordering them on Amazon is fast,easy, and economical.
